                    },
                    "body": "Assigning this issue to Robin Skoglund as he's the maintainer (and creator) of Zend_Navigation.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-24T17:35:17.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-24T17:35:17.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36504",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jgornick",
                        "name": "jgornick",
                        "displayName": "Joe Gornick",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Robin, thoughts on this?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jgornick",
                        "name": "jgornick",
                        "displayName": "Joe Gornick",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-25T10:44:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-25T10:44:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36506",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=robinsk",
                        "name": "robinsk",
                        "displayName": "Robin Skoglund",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "My thoughts: the rendering might be changed to some sort of decorators for ZF 2.0. This issue might be related to ZF-7003. Maybe I (or someone else) should create a wiki page for Zend_Navigation 2.0 to gather feedback and thoughts on changes\/improvements.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=robinsk",
                        "name": "robinsk",
                        "displayName": "Robin Skoglund",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-25T10:53:11.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-25T10:53:11.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36508",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jgornick",
                        "name": "jgornick",
                        "displayName": "Joe Gornick",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Robin, thanks for the prompt response!\r\n\r\nDecorators for 2.0 sounds like a great idea!  That would give complete control of the output produced by the view helpers.  I can dig it.\r\n\r\nIn the meantime, the output produced by view helper is sufficient for most use cases, however, in a situation when you want to apply background images to a link and hide the text, this is where it is limited.  I think what I'm trying to ask for is a poor mans attempt at a decorator.  However, this decorator only affects the label.\r\n\r\nAnother example could look like:\r\n\r\n$this->navigation()->menu(null, array(\r\n    'labelWrapper' => array(\r\n        'element' => 'span',\r\n        'class' => 'label-span'\r\n    )\r\n);\r\n\r\nThat would then wrap the label with a span element and add the class of label-span.  Any other options you supply would be translated to attribute on the wrapper element.\r\n\r\nJust trying to brainstorm here.  Maybe for now, I can simply write my own navigation menu view helper that add the ability, but I think we should discuss the idea of adding decorators of some sorts to the navigation view helpers in ZF 2.0.\r\n\r\nThanks!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jgornick",
                        "name": "jgornick",
                        "displayName": "Joe Gornick",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-25T11:49:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-25T11:49:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40825",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=djvirgen",
                        "name": "djvirgen",
                        "displayName": "Hector Virgen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree and also need an inner <span> for styling purposes. I've tried using Javascript to inject spans inside of the anchors, but this breaks for non-JS browsers.\r\n\r\nI've also tried providing my own view helper that extends Zend_View_Helper_Navigation_Menu to overload the htmlify() method, but my helper is not being picked up. I believe this is because the navigation helper adds its helper path to the end of the stack instead of the beginning. Since the helper paths are LIFO, it finds the built-in ZF helper instead of using mine.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=djvirgen",
                        "name": "djvirgen",
                        "displayName": "Hector Virgen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-06-01T16:04:25.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-06-01T16:04:25.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50204",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=frosch",
                        "name": "frosch",
                        "displayName": "Frank Br\u00fcckner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think we will wait for the implementation of rendering in [Zend_Form 2.0|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/wiki\/display\/ZFDEV2\/RFC+-+Forms#RFC-Forms-Rendering] and then we adapt this for the navigation view helpers.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=frosch",
                        "name": "frosch",
                        "displayName": "Frank Br\u00fcckner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-04-05T14:20:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-04-05T14:20:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/53086",
